vocabulary.definition: specially made according to a particular person's requirements
vocabulary.example: The tailor created a bespoke suit for the customer.

vocabulary.definition: a model of a product that can be tested, improved, and used to develop a better product
vocabulary.example: The company developed a prototype of the new smartphone before mass production.

vocabulary.definition: inability or refusal to accept that something is true or real
vocabulary.example: She looked at the surprise gift in disbelief.

vocabulary.definition: playing with something carelessly, not for a serious reason
vocabulary.example: The children were mucking about in the garden.

vocabulary.definition: artificial body parts, such as arms, legs, feet, or eyes, used to replace a missing natural part
vocabulary.example: The athlete was able to compete again with the help of advanced prosthetics.

vocabulary.definition: taking a lot of time to do
vocabulary.example: The manual painting process is very time-consuming.
